SUMMARY—Establishing certain notification and reporting
requirements concerning pilot programs that research
transcranial magnetic stimulation or electromagnetic
brain pulse treatment. (BDR S-865)
FISCAL NOTE: Effect on Local Government: May have Fiscal Impact.
Effect on the State: Yes.
~
EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to mental health; establishing certain notification
and reporting requirements concerning pilot programs that
research transcranial magnetic stimulation or
electromagnetic brain pulse treatment; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 This bill requires a practitioner or entity that conducts a pilot program that
2 researches transcranial magnetic stimulation or electromagnetic brain pulse
3 treatment to submit certain notifications and reports to the Director of the
4 Legislative Counsel Bureau. Specifically, this bill requires the practitioner or entity,
5 before commencing the pilot program, to submit to the Director a notification that
6 contains certain information relating to the practitioner or entity, the methodology
7 of the research and the research subjects. Additionally, once the pilot program
8 commences, this bill requires the practitioner or entity to submit a report once each
9 calendar quarter to the Director which contains certain information related to the
10 research subjects. Finally, upon the completion of the pilot program, this bill
11 requires the practitioner or entity to submit a final report to the Director that
12 contains certain information related to the results of the pilot program and any
13 corresponding recommendations related to the research.
