THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. In addition to complying with any other
2 applicable state or federal requirements, and except as otherwise
3 provided in subsection 2, a practitioner or entity who implements a
4 pilot program in this State shall submit to the Director of the
5 Legislative Counsel Bureau:
6 (a) Before any research is conducted under the pilot program, a
7 notification that contains:
8 (1) The name of the practitioner or entity conducting the
9 research under the pilot program;
10 (2) A description of the purpose, scope and objectives of the
11 research to be conducted under the pilot program, which must
12 include, without limitation, an identification of whether transcranial
13 magnetic stimulation or electromagnetic brain pulse treatment, or
14 both, will be used in the pilot program;
15 (3) The number of research subjects anticipated to be
16 involved in the pilot program and a general description of the
17 characteristics of each research subject;
18 (4) Any location at which the research will be conducted
19 under the pilot program; and
20 (5) An identification of any licenses, registrations and other
21 approvals that are necessary to conduct the research under the pilot
22 program and proof that the practitioner or entity has obtained all
23 such licenses, registrations and approvals;
24 (b) At least once each calendar quarter while research is being
25 conducted under the pilot program, a report concerning the research,
26 which must include, without limitation:
27 (1) The number of research subjects participating in the pilot
28 program in the immediately preceding calendar quarter;
29 (2) Aggregated demographic information concerning the
30 research subjects;
31 (3) Baseline health and mental health assessments of the
32 research subjects;
33 (4) Outcomes of treatment, including, without limitation,
34 longitudinal data after the conclusion of treatments; and
35 (5) Data relating to any monitoring that is performed for
36 ethical or safety purposes; and
37 (c) After the pilot program has concluded, a report on the results
38 of the research conducted under the pilot program and any
39 corresponding recommendations relating to the research.
40 2. If multiple practitioners or entities conduct research under
41 the same pilot program, the practitioners or entities may submit a
42 single report pursuant to subsection 1 concerning the pilot program.
